<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Pekan 05 Assignment - 110-Muhammad Mansur Adam</title>
    
    <!-- Link for CSS Icons (Requirement: CSS Icons) -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com">

    <style>
        /* --- 1. CSS Comments --- */
        /* This internal stylesheet covers all Week 05 requirements */

        /* --- 2. CSS Colors & Backgrounds --- */
        body {
            background-color: #f0f2f5; /* Backgrounds */
            color: #1c1e21;            /* Colors */
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; /* Fonts */
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        /* --- 3. CSS Box Model (Margins, Padding, Height/Width, Borders) --- */
        .main-container {
            max-width: 800px;          /* Width */
            margin: 40px auto;         /* Margins */
            padding: 25px;             /* Padding */
            background-color: #ffffff;
            border: 2px solid #3498db; /* Borders */
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-sizing: border-box;    /* Box Model */
            outline: 3px solid #e1e4e8; /* Outline */
        }

        /* --- 4. CSS Text & Fonts --- */
        h1 {
            text-align: center;        /* Text alignment */
            text-transform: uppercase; /* Text transformation */
            letter-spacing: 2px;
            color: #2c3e50;
            font-size: 24px;           /* Fonts */
        }

        .name-header {
            text-align: center;        /* Center alignment */
            font-size: 28px;           /* Fonts */
            color: #2c3e50;
            margin: 20px 0;            /* Margins */
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .description {
            line-height: 1.6;
            text-indent: 30px;
        }

        /* --- 5. CSS Links --- */
        .assignment-link {
            color: #3498db;
            text-decoration: none;     /* Text decoration */
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .assignment-link:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
            color: #2980b9;
        }

        /* --- 6. CSS Lists --- */
        .topic-list {
            list-style-type: square;   /* Lists styling */
            padding-left: 20px;
        }
        .topic-list li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        /* --- 7. CSS Tables --- */
        .data-table {
            width: 100%;               /* Width */
            border-collapse: collapse; /* Table specific property */
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .data-table th, .data-table td {
            border: 1px solid #ddd;    /* Borders */
            padding: 12px;             /* Padding */
            text-align: left;
        }
        .data-table th {
            background-color: #3498db;
            color: white;
        }

        /* --- 8. CSS Errors --- */
        /* CSS is forgiving. If I wrote 'colour: red;' (Error), 
           the browser would ignore it. Below is valid code. */
        .error-note {
            color: #e74c3c;
            font-style: italic;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="main-container">
        <h2 class="name-header">Assignment Week 05</h2>
        <h1>Muhammad Mansur Adam</h1>
        
        <p class="description">
            This page demonstrates the <strong>CSS Box Model</strong>, including margins, 
            padding, and borders. Below is a showcase of the required topics.
        </p>

        <h3><i class="fas fa-list"></i> CSS Topics Included:</h3>
        <ul class="topic-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Text, Fonts, and Colors</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Backgrounds and Outlines</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Lists and Tables</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Example Table</h3>
        <table class="data-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Topic</th>
                    <th>Status</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>CSS Tutorials</td>
                    <td>Completed</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Learn More...</td>
                    <td><a href="" class="assignment-link">https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_intro.asp</a></td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="error-note">Note: CSS Errors are handled by browser validation.</p>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
